  <li itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
    <strong><span itemprop="name">What's the latest blog post?</span></strong>
    <div itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
      I used to write blog posts semi-regularly… now not so much! Most recently I wrote <strong itemprop="text"><a href="{{ latestPost.url }}">{{ latestPost.data.title }}</a></strong>.
      You can <a href="/blog">view a list of all blog posts here</a>.
    </div>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Albums this month</strong>
    <div>
      This month I've been enjoying

      {% for album in lastfm %}
        {% if loop.last %} and {% endif %}
        {% imgBookCover album.image[0]['#text'], album.name + " Cover", [35, 75], "nowList__album", "1.1em" %}
        <a href="{{ album.url }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>{{ album.name }}</strong></a> by <em>{{ album.artist.name }}</em>
        {% if loop.last == false %}, {% endif %}
      {% endfor %}.

      <span class="js-nowPlaying"></span>

      My music listening gets logged in <a href="https://last.fm/user/jamesdoc">Last.fm</a> by <a href="/blog/2022/sleeve">Sleeve</a>.

    </div>
  </li>

  <li itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
    <strong><span itemprop="name">What are you reading?</span></strong>
    <div itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
      <span itemprop="text">Right now I'm reading
      {% for book in currentBooks %}
        <strong>{{ book.name }}</strong> by <em>{{ book.additional.author }}</em>{% if loop.last != true %},{% else %}.{% endif %}
      {% endfor %} I keep track of all the books I'm reading through a big reading list in Trello and then pull them into this site.
      You can <a href="/reading-list">view the full reading list</a>.
      </span>
    </div>
  </li>
</ul>

